<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1364">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/194.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s February 25. Military Governor Chao replies on behalf of
                                General Villa to my note directed to the latter urging an
                                investigation of the killing of Jose and Agustin Gonzalez that the
                                state government is not authorized under orders prevailing to treat
                                on matters of international bearing and that questions of this
                                character should be addressed to the First Chief of the
                                revolution.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>